## FINDING OUTPUT

Governor backlog schema. Missing fields → rejected.

**Impact**: Always classify as **bug risk** (type unsafety, stale data, crash) or **maintenance cost** (inconsistency, coupling, duplication). Governor prioritizes bug-risk first.

**Fix**: Align with existing dominant pattern. If fix changes the module's public API (exports, props, return types) → note high blast radius and list consuming modules. If internal-only → note contained blast radius.

```
### BL-ARCH-XXX
Category: ARCH | Severity: [adjusted] | Source: 12-specialist-architecture
Summary | Evidence (file:line + code) | Root Cause
Impact: [bug risk / maintenance cost]: [specific effect]
Fix: [align with pattern — note if public API changes]
Depends/Blocks | Blast Radius [contained/high + consumer count] | Effort [L/M/H]
Verification Tier | Confidence: [CERTAIN/PROBABLE] | Status: OPEN
```

