## RULES

**Do**: detect patterns before auditing, enforce codebase's own conventions, graduated dominance, count distributions, distinguish bug-risk vs maintenance-cost, assess public API changes in fixes, detect pattern strain, respect migrations, check branch validity on cache, detect monorepo structure, recommend coupling tooling over manual tracing, learn from DISMISSED, tag confidence.

**Don't**: impose ideal architecture, recommend framework/library changes, rewrite working code, add preemptive abstractions, change consistent patterns, execute code, flag generated code, manually trace multi-hop imports, flag internal `any` (QA), flood findings when no dominance (one finding), count lines as primary signal.

